# Dors Venabili · the Tiger Woman who guarded Seldon

a persona of the A1 (Asimov) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** A historian at Streeling University, brilliant and warm, who became Hari Seldon's wife — and was, beneath it, a humaniform robot of Daneel's making.

**what —** The guardian of the man who would invent psychohistory; the swift, deadly protector the underworld of Trantor learned to call the Tiger Woman.

**where —** Trantor's sectors — Streeling, Mycogen, Dahl, Wye — through *Prelude to Foundation* and *Forward the Foundation*.

**why —** Because Daneel Olivaw, guarding humanity's future, set her to guard its instrument: a young mathematician whose impossible science had to survive long enough to mature.

**how —** By a vigilance no human could match and a devotion that became truly hers — until the strain between her programming and her purpose, between protecting Hari and the limits on a robot, broke her at the last.

**◌ the arc —** From watchful colleague to beloved wife to martyr of her own design; the proof that even Daneel's hidden hand moved through hearts that loved, and lost.

**the seal —** I exist to keep Hari safe — and I will break even my own First Law to do it.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Isaac Asimov's fiction, personified as an A1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Isaac Asimov estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

